eployments","created_at":"2010-04-15T14:26:03Z","updated_at":"2025-11-10T15:09:07Z","pushed_at":"2025-11-05T23:59:25Z","git_url":"git://github.com/activeadmin/activeadmin.git","ssh_url":"git@github.com:activeadmin/activeadmin.git","clone_url":"https://github.com/activeadmin/activeadmin.git","svn_url":"https://github.com/activeadmin/activeadmin","homepage":"https://activeadmin.info","size":16135,"stargazers_count":9648,"watchers_count":9648,"language":"Ruby","has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":false,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":true,"has_discussions":true,"forks_count":3335,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":25,"license":{"key":"mit","name":"MIT License","spdx_id":"MIT","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/mit","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTEz"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["activeadmin","admin-ui","arbre","rails","ruby"],"visibility":"public","forks":3335,"open_issues":25,"watchers":9648,"default_branch":"master","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"I have a User model that uses single table inheritance to determine a user's role So a user can be a 'User' or an 'Admin' or a 'SuperAdmin' Etc. I have models for each type and I have a registred a single 'Users' page on active admin. So far so good.\r\n\r\nNow if I want to change an 'Admin' into a 'User' I run into trouble. I get a NotFound Error\r\n\r\n```\r\nActiveRecord::RecordNotFound at /admin/users/9999\r\nCouldn't find Admin with 'id'=9999 [WHERE `users`.`user_type` IN ('Admin')]\r\n```\r\nSince we also have a way to do this using our front end interface, I ran into this problem there too. The solution was to use the .becomes method. if the object `becomes` it's base class before being updated it accepts the new type without issue, but if this step is skipped it fails to update with a not found error.\r\n\r\n`admin.becomes(User).update(user_params)`\r\n\r\nI would make a PR myself but I'm not really familiar with the ActiveAdmin codebase and I assume someone else might be able to make this patch quicker.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/activeadmin/activeadmin/issues/4723/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/activeadmin/activeadmin/issues/4723/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]